|CKBAn Inventory of Tricks, Devices, and Plausible Denials|000

Use 'chskills' for the full ledger: spell-point cost, recovery time, Rank,
road, and trade requirements. 'chskills available' shows only the tricks you
can pull off right now.

At Rank 35 and every five Ranks through 100, Drina opens another scheme.
Schemes are horizontal modifications to these tricks rather than new road
ranks. Use 'schemes' to inspect the catalogue and active cloak notes.

Misdirection

  confuse [foe]
    Talk, feint, and insist until a foe's attention goes somewhere harmless.
    Available from Rank 1; deeper Misdirection makes the lie stick.

  suckerpunch [foe]
    Available from Rank 1. Cash in an opening with one profoundly unfair
    melee hit. Misdirection adds force and eventually brings a second weapon
    into the argument.

  distract [foe]
    Rank 3, Misdirection 2. Throw your voice somewhere inconvenient. With
    enough practice, a foe may briefly forget whom they were fighting.

  avoid
    Rank 4, Misdirection 3. Revive the Confidence's fancy footwork and make
    yourself substantially harder to hit for a short, buff-visible window.

Volatility

  brewacid
    Rank 2, Volatility 1, Alchemy 25. Prepare the owner-bound base flask used
    by Cook Ash. It can also be thrown by Charlatans with poor impulse control.

  brewelement <fire|ice|lightning>
    Rank 3, Volatility 2, Alchemy 75. Bottle some deeply uncooperative weather
    for throwing. Every successful throw splashes part of the blast back.

  cookash <grey|red|blue|mixed>
    Rank 2, Volatility 1. Empty every relevant ash from a corpse burner into
    an acid flask. Quaffing grants an ash-specific combat rush shown in buffs.

  concoct <red salt|blue mixer|cutting bitters>
    Rank 2, Volatility 2. Prepare a seasoning for carried food or drink.
    Benefits vary; fine print is compulsory.

Contraband

  loadweapon <weapon> with <dazzling|oiled|silvered|flaming|frozen|poisoned|shocking>
    Rank 2. Fit a temporary and dubiously safe treatment to an unwielded,
    ordinary weapon. Better tricks require deeper Contraband and trade skill.

  stretchpoison <poison> onto <weapon>
    Rank 3, Contraband 2, Alchemy 100. Make one proper poison last longer at
    reduced strength. The poison always gets one vote about your technique.

  pocketsand [foe]
    Rank 4, Contraband 2. Attempt to blind a nearby foe using tactical grit
    stored in a pocket no tailor admits sewing.

Caravan stock

  Ordinary throwing darts remain for sale and use 'throw <target>'. Acid and
  elemental flasks are now brewed abilities rather than shop stock. The old
  poison-dart recipe, flying potion, smoke packet, and special bottle belonged
  to the closed Alchemist/Illusionist ledgers and are no longer sold.
